In this article, President Trump discusses his administration's commitment to fighting for American workers and addressing unfair trade practices. He emphasizes the negative impact of years of unfair trade on American families and the loss of manufacturing jobs. Trump highlights the $12.5 trillion trade deficit and the decline of the middle class due to other countries taking advantage of the United States. He criticizes previous leaders for not taking action against economic aggression and surrendering to unfair practices. Trump mentions a thorough investigation into China's unfair trade practices and proposes tariffs as a way to protect American industries. He also vows to no longer tolerate unfair and non-reciprocal trading practices with any country and promises to use all available authorities to protect farmers. Trump advocates for fair and reciprocal trade where countries open their markets equally and all sides play by the rules. He concludes by expressing his commitment to making America wealthy again.